subSubSection.paragraph:
Ovate to elongate ovate, macropterous (
figure 1
). Head from above somewhat semi-lunar to weakly triangular, about 2.18–2.56x as broad as long; in front more or less quadrangular (
figure 2
), about 1.19–1.26x as broad as high. Frons at base somewhat rugose with shallow punctures; rather strongly depressed, producing somewhat broad ridge-like impressions on either side along mesal eye margins; distinctly tumid convex at apex, finely transversely rugose with impressed oval patches posteriorly on either side of disk, smooth. Colouration variable; disk in some specimens dark-reddish to black with occiput, postgenae, juga, broad arc-like lateral maginal bands on frons, all pale reddish to yellow-brown; in others, in addition base of frons extensively pale; and in yet others, vertex is similarly pale. Entire head disk generally shining, pubescent with short semi-erect yellow-brown hairs. Ocelli protuberant, dark-reddish with distinct reddish surrounding annuli; about 2.0–2.25 width of each apart. Gena subexcavated, about 0.33x as high as eye. Eyes dark-reddish, obscurely hairy, emarginate behind ocelli. Antennal segment I dark reddish-brown to black, somewhat paler at tip, and/or broadly pale at base; about as thick as II at apex. II yellow-brown with slight reddish tinge, gently recurved outwards; about 1.5x as thick towards apical fifth as remainder of segment; pubescent with golden semi-reclining hairs subequal or shorter than segment is thick. III linear, similarly coloured and about 0.5x as thick as II at base; pubescent with golden semi-erect hairs about twice as long as segment thickness. IV yellow-brown with reddish tinge, fusiform; pubescent with golden semi-reclining hairs interspersed with much longer erect hairs about 2.5x as long as segment thickness.
